{"build_type":"library","description":"Tail-recursive worklist DRIVER (repurposed from the former -iteration). Pops 4xi64 task records [type,a,b,c] off the explicit lowering stack and dispatches them at CONSTANT native-stack depth (self-call in tail position, TCO). Types: 1=ARRAY-STEP[arr,i,n] walks a flat instruction array preserving the exact pair-TCO logic and per-instruction step-budget of the original recursion, pushing the i+1/i+2 continuation before dispatching the item so a conditional_branch's pushed continuations run before it; 2=EMIT-JMP emits a jmp op to the carried label; 3=EMIT-LABEL emits a label op with the carried name. Empty stack (g_wl_top==0) terminates. Replaces the deep native recursion that overflowed the packed stack segment.","module_name":"lower-instruction-array-towards-native-operations-iteration","package_name":"lower-instruction-array-towards-native-operations-iteration","function_definitions":{"lower-instruction-array-towards-native-operations-iteration":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"ops","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"T_ARRAY","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declara